title: Princess Anne Attends Remembrance Sunday Service During Sydney Visit | 10 News
description: Princess Anne pulled on her army greens to meet hundreds of Australian servicemen and women during a day of official duties in Sydney. She commemorated the hundredth anniversary of the Royal Australian Signal Corps at a garden party and spoke of her hopes for enduring peace during a special Remembrance Day service. title: Liberal Senator Andrew Bragg Threatens To Quit Frontbench If Net Zero Policy Is Dropped | 10 News
description: A prominent Liberal senator has threatened to quit the front bench if the party walks away from its international commitment to cut greenhouse gas emissions and combat global warming. Andrew Bragg says it is "ridiculous" to drop Net Zero, setting up a fiery climate clash with his more conservative colleagues this week. title: Oscar Piastri Crashes Out As Lando Norris Extends F1 Championship Lead In Brazil GP | 10 News
description: Oscar Piastri started the Brazil weekend one point behind Lando Norris, and has now slipped even further behind in the race for the Formula 1 World Championship. The Aussie crashed out of the Sprint race in Brazil and only managed fourth in qualifying. The race was then won by his teammate, with Lando Norris then nailing pole for tomorrow's main event. title: NSW Police And Premier Chris Minns Up Against Legal Minefield Over Neo-Nazi Rally | 10 News+
description: New South Wales residents are shocked after it was revealed that police allowed a Neo-Nazi protest outside the State Parliament in Sydney. Premier Chris Minns and NSW Police now face a legal minefield, as they determine whether or not the ‘White Australia’ group broke any racial vilification laws. The Premier hopes to add to existing laws, or make new ones, to stop the far-right white supremacist group from rallying again. title: Neo-Nazis Outside NSW Parliament, US Government Shutdown, Princess Anne In Australia | 10 News+
description: Despite the growing split in the Coalition over net zero policy, a Liberal MP has joined her Nationals colleague in a stunning musical performance in Parliament. Angie Bell played the saxophone while Sam Birrell took on the vocals, singing “they can never tear us apart”. 10 News+ spoke to Angie Bell about the unexpected display of unity.  New South Wales residents are shocked after it was revealed that police allowed a Neo-Nazi protest outside the State Parliament in Sydney. Premier Chris Minns and NSW Police now face a legal minefield, as they determine whether or not the ‘White Australia’ group broke any racial vilification laws. The Premier hopes to add to existing laws, or make new ones, to stop the far-right white supremacist group from rallying again.  The United States’ first government shutdown in seven years is now entering its 39th day, eclipsing the previous record. The shutdown is not only crippling the US economy, but is also causing flight chaos, forcing over 700,000 public servants to work without pay, and leaving up to 41 million Americans who usually rely on food stamps to miss meals.  Australia’s whale-watching community is excited over the spotting of a young albino whale off the country’s east coast. The one-year-old humpback named Siale was born in Tonga and is currently cruising north, last spotted heading to Sydney. White whales are incredibly rare, with the last known example in the Pacific Ocean not having been spotted for five years. title: Three Dead After Wild Seas Smash Island of Tenerife | 10 News
description: Three people have died and a further 15 were injured after the popular Spanish holiday island of Tenerife was battered by rough seas.  One man reportedly fell into the water north of the island, and was airlifted to hospital where he was subsequently pronounced dead.  Elsewhere, a man was pronounced dead after being found floating in the water south of the island, and a woman reportedly suffered a fatal heart attack after being swept into the ocean along with 10 other people at Puerto de la Cruz.  Local officials have warned tourists and residents alike to stay away from coastal paths and to not take pictures or videos of the wild swells. Turbulent weather in the region is expected to worsen over the coming days. title: Two Dead, Millions Evacuated As Super Typhoon Fung-Wong Hits Philippines | 10 News
description: At least two people have died, and one million people evacuated as Super Typhoon Fung-wong made landfall in the Philippines on Sunday.  Videos posted on social media show the deadly storm battering the nation with winds of up to 230kmph, torrential rain, and dangerous storm surges.  Authorities said the storm, known locally as Uwan, is expected to head towards Taiwan.  It was the 21st storm this year to hit the country and comes less than a week after Typhoon Kalmaegi left more than 200 people dead. title: Dingo Snatches Shark From Fisherman On Queensand's K'gari Island | 10 News
description: A dingo has been captured on video sneakily beating a fisherman to his catch from the shallows on Queensland’s K’gari Island.  It’s understood the fisherman hooked a baby shark and tried to release it twice before the dingo darted in and ran back to shore with it in its mouth.  The incident happened on Saturday night just north of Eurong.
